You need to have Python 2.7 installed in order to run this script.

Google Developer credentials go into credentials.json

Channel names (not necessarily always the channel username) to watch and post video comments to go in channels.txt with only one channel per line.

The comment that you want to have posted on each video goes in comment.txt

The redirect URI in your Google App settings needs to be set to "http://localhost:8090" in order to authenticate your Youtube account with the bot. 

Once you've authenticated, the bot will create a file called credentials.dat. Only delete this file if you think that you need to have your account reauthenticated, otherwise do not move or delete it.

